# HackerOne precedent index — seed rows for A3.
#
# Field semantics:
#   program      — HackerOne program handle, or "generic" for cross-program median
#   class        — vulnerability class matching ArtifactMatrix canonical name
#   severity     — P1..P5
#   bounty       — number: confirmed paid amount (0 = confirmed unpaid; still a precedent)
#                  null: amount undisclosed; row is retained as context but NOT citable for a figure
#   url          — real HackerOne disclosure URL, OR a placeholder:// scheme for seed stubs
#   closed_as    — "resolved" rows are citable precedents; "duplicate", "informative",
#                  "not-applicable" are anti-evidence and are FILTERED OUT at lookup time
#   date         — ISO-8601 date of closure
#   placeholder  — true for seed/stub rows (hand-coded medians, not real disclosures);
#                  the lookup returns null for placeholder rows unless --allow-placeholder
#                  is passed. This keeps Advocate citations honest until real data arrives.
#   notes        — free-form curator notes (methodology, source, quirks)
#
# Curator rules:
#   - On duplicate (program, class, severity) keys, the FIRST matching row wins.
#     Keep keys unique per (program, class, severity).
#   - Remove placeholder:true rows as real disclosures arrive to replace them.
#   - Only add rows with closed_as == "resolved" unless you are intentionally tracking
#     anti-evidence (in which case Advocate won't cite them anyway).
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
